# Postgres example flows

These flows demonstrate the use of the
`node-red-contrib-postgres-multi` node.

## Setup

For the flows in this tab,
you'll need a PostgreSQL table like so:

    begin;
    create table mytable
    (
        id integer not null,
        message character varying(20)
    );
    create unique index on mytable (id);
    commit;

Then you'll need to configure the postgres
blocks to have access to this database and table.

